  "prompt": "Is there a Church that doesn't believe in Trinity?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several religious groups and denominations that do not believe in the Trinity:\n\n1. Jehovah's Witnesses\n- Reject the Trinity doctrine\n- Believe Jesus is a created being, separate from God\n- Consider the Holy Spirit a force, not a person\n\n2. Oneness Pentecostals (Apostolic Pentecostals)\n- Believe in Jesus only\n- Hold that God is one person who manifests in different modes\n\n3. Unitarian Churches\n- Believe God is one person\n- See Jesus as a prophet or spiritual leader, not divine\n- Emphasize the unity of God\n\n4. Mormons (The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints)\n- Have a different concept of the Godhead\n- Believe the Father, Son, and Holy Spirit are separate beings\n\n5. Some branches of Judaism\n- Do not recognize Jesus as divine\n- Strictly maintain monotheism\n\n6. Islam\n- Strongly rejects the Trinity\n- Believes in absolute monotheism\n- Considers Jesus a prophet, not divine\n\nThese groups interpret biblical texts differently and have theological perspectives that do not align with the traditional Christian doctrine of the Trinity.",
